Bash file to do end to end for user similarity.
Takes a single number as an argument, k nearest neighbors to use.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/ndejaco/Traffic

Adding my files

data2json.py takes three arguments:
 #k-nearest neighbors #input file made by vectorizeUsers.py #name of output file
 Will output a json file to use with forceGraph.html, the general output file
 name I have been using is "similarity.json"

forceGraph.html: This is the code to create the force graph based on the json file
  Only significant value you might want to change is the json file to be read in. Currently hardcoded to 'similarity.json'

similarity.json: An example output from data2json.py, currently with 3 nearest neighbors

vectorizeUsers.py: Two arguments #inFile, this is the structured traffic data file #output file. This output file will then be used with data2json.py
